README - ID3 Classification Mining
----------------------------------

This program implements the ID3 classification mining algorithim in Java.

The code consists of the following Java files:
	ID3Mining.java 	- main(), loadDB(), getTargetClasses(), gain(), 		
										entropy(), entropyS(), log2(), id3(), printTree()
	AVList.java			- AVList(), add(), toString(), setUniqueValues(), 		
										getUniqueValues(), getUniqueCount(), getAttribute(), setGain(), getGain(), isBinary()
	DataBase.java		- DataBase(), getAttributes(), addRow(), getData(), 	
										proportion(), numRowsWithValue(), getRowsWithValue(), allMatchClass()
	Target.java			- Target(), getters, setters
	Node.java				- Node(), addNode(), getters, setters
	
	ID3Mining.java						 	- The main part of the program, does the bulk
																of the work.
	AVList.java									- Represents the attribute=value pairs found
																in the data in the form of an attribute and
																all the values associated.
	DataBase.java 							- Represents the data for the program in the 
																form of all of the rows in a list.
	Target.java 								- Represents the target attribute.
	Node.java										- Represents a node of the tree structure 
																generated by the algorithm.
	
Program Structure:
		
	main()---->loadDB
				
				---->isBinary
				
				---->getTargetClasses
								---->setUniqueValues
								---->getUniqueValues
								---->numRowsWithValue
				
				---->id3
								---->allMatchClass
								---->numRowsWithValue
								---->gain
												---->entropyS
																---->proportion
												---->entropy
																---->proportion
				
				---->printTree
				
Run the program:
	bluenose: javax *.java
	bluenose: java ID3Mining

The result is stored in the file Rules, to view the result:                         
  bluenose: more Rules 